law.text:
This title applies to the following types of ballot questions:
a question relating to:
the creation or adoption of a new Constitution or the calling of a constitutional convention; or
an amendment pursuant to Article XIV of the Maryland Constitution;
referral of an enactment of the General Assembly pursuant to Article XVI of the Maryland Constitution;
a question pursuant to Article XI-A of the Maryland Constitution relating to:
the creation of a charter home rule county government;
the approval of a county charter; or
the amendment of a county charter;
a question relating to the creation of a code home rule county government pursuant to Article XI-F of the Maryland Constitution;
a question relating to the alteration of county boundaries or the creation of a new county pursuant to Article XIII of the Maryland Constitution;
a question referred to the voters pursuant to an enactment of the General Assembly;
a question on an enactment of a charter county pursuant to Article 25A, § 8 of the Code or a code county pursuant to Article 25B, § 10 of the Code;
a question relating to the incorporation of a new municipality pursuant to Article 23A, § 21 of the Code;
a question on the issuance of a bond pursuant to § 9-934 of the Environment Article; and
any other question that will be voted on in an election conducted pursuant to this article.
